  source = {makes the real problem invisible, and second, it can be harmful to the fat individual. Let’s look at the question in more detail. The definition of a disease has been much debated over the last decades. Disease tends to be defined by the relation to the sick individual, not to some situation in the society as a whole. Historically disease is related to individual sufferings and we show compassion with those who are ill. The role of the doctor is to cure and to care. He takes on this role by reacting to the sufferings of his fellow man (Jonsen,1990) By relating the obesity problem to a disease and to the patient we personalize the problem},
